  "texts": [
    "Rational abstract Burnside rings In this section, we survey Yoshida's theory of abstract Burnside rings over the rational numbers [Yos87].",
    "It describes a process of assigning a ring to a finite skeletal category, which in the case of the orbit category of a finite group 𝐺 recovers (Theorem 2.7) the rational Burnside ring 𝐴(𝐺) from rational equivariant algebra [Yos87, Example 3.3.(a)].",
    "We work rationally since our applications are rational, but the theory holds more generally, see e.g., [Yos87, YOT18].",
    "Let C denote a finite skeletal category, i.e., a category with finitely many objects, finitely many morphisms and such that if 𝑐 𝑑, then 𝑐 = 𝑑.",
    "Write Q C for the product 𝑐∈C Q and denote by 𝐴 Q (C) the free Q-module generated by the set of object of C. Define the Burnside homomorphism to be the Q-linear map, 𝜙: 𝐴 Q (C) -→ Q C, 𝑑 ↦ -→ (|C(𝑐, 𝑑)|) 𝑐∈C, where C(𝑐, 𝑑) is the set of morphisms in C from 𝑐 to 𝑑."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}